text: The Dii Consentes (Latin: "[the] council of the divine") was the principal group of deities within Ancient Roman religion, equivalent to the Twelve Olympians. As listed by the poet Ennius in the late 3rd Century BC,Ennius, fragment 45 = Apuleius, De deo Socratis, 2.28â€“29. they consisted of: * Jupiter, Juno, Vesta, Minerva, Ceres, Apollo, Diana, Venus, Mars, Vulcan, Mercury, and Neptune. ==References== Category:Roman gods and goddesses
title: Dii Consentes
